                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>New York June 24th&#47;95<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#59;<lb/>
                <sic>Deer</sic> Sir&#33;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>By advice<lb/> of Rev. Dr. B. Drachman I<lb/> address myself to you to<lb/> seek your aid in obtaining<lb/> a place as teacher of Hebrew<lb/> or mathematics<lb/></p>
            <p>I refer to Rev. Dr. Hildesheimer<lb/> of Berlin to my knowledge<lb/> of Hebrew if you will be<lb/> kind enough to inquire of<lb/> him.<lb/>
                Mathematics I <sic>studiet</sic> at<lb/> the University of Wurzburg<lb/> of which I am a graduate.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr. I. S Schwatt of the<lb/> University of Pennsylvania<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>is my reference to my know&#45;<lb/>ledge of mathematics&#44; who<lb/> held a treatise of mine<lb/> on the subject &#34;Reduction<lb/> der quadpatisichen quinter.<lb/>naener positiven Formen.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>In Paris I had a Hebrew<lb/> School under the protection<lb/> of Grand Rabbi Zadar Kahn<lb/></p> 
            <p>At present I am teaching<lb/> Hebrew in the English<lb/> language at the<lb/> Hebrew School 227. E 104th St.<lb/> I send enclosed copies of<lb/> my recommendations.<lb/></p>
            <p>Respectfully yours<lb/>
                K. Mekish<lb/></p>
            <p>238 E 119th St<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
